WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:07.433
<i>[ Chorus ]
# The Simpsons #</i>

00:09.000 --> 00:15.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:18.215 --> 00:20.115
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

00:24.989 --> 00:28.049
<i>[ Whistle Blowing ]</i>

00:30.527 --> 00:32.427
[ Beeping ]

00:38.168 --> 00:40.102
## [Jazzy Solo ]

01:00.157 --> 01:02.057
[ Beeping ]

01:02.159 --> 01:04.059
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.429 --> 01:07.363
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:22.212 --> 01:26.581
- [ Announcer] You're watching PBS.
- ## [ Trumpet Flourish ]

01:26.684 --> 01:30.211
- You're watching PBS?
- Hey, I'm as surprised as you...

01:30.321 --> 01:33.950
but I've stumbled upon
the most delicious British sitcom.

01:34.058 --> 01:35.958
<i>''Do Shut Up''?</i>

01:36.060 --> 01:39.120
It's about a hard-drinking
yet loving family of soccer hooligans.

01:39.229 --> 01:41.789
If they're not having
a go with a bird...

01:41.899 --> 01:44.265
they're having a row with a wanker.

01:44.368 --> 01:46.268
Cheeky.

01:46.370 --> 01:48.804
<i>[ Man ]
#No feeling #</i>

01:48.906 --> 01:51.238
<i>#No feeling #</i>

01:51.342 --> 01:53.242
<i>- Ahh!
- #No feeling #</i>

01:53.344 --> 01:55.209
<i>-Jolly sodding X-mas, Major.
- #For anybody else ##</i>

01:55.312 --> 01:58.713
- Choke on it!
- [ Both Laughing ]

01:58.816 --> 02:01.284
Oh, crikey!

02:01.385 --> 02:04.252
You gave me a smash
on the noggin last year.

02:05.356 --> 02:07.256
- [ Grunting ]
- [ Groaning ]

02:07.358 --> 02:09.588
Not in my parlor, you don't.

02:09.693 --> 02:12.127
- Aah! Me eyes!
- I'm scalded, I am!

02:12.229 --> 02:14.754
[ Both Laughing ]

02:14.865 --> 02:18.323
- The mother's the voice of reason.
- Here come the cricket bats.

02:19.903 --> 02:22.235
You don't have the cobbles.

02:22.339 --> 02:24.807
- [ Both Snarling ]
- [ Chuckling ]

02:24.908 --> 02:28.639
Classic. Not hard to see why
it's England's longest-running series.

02:28.746 --> 02:30.941
And today we're showing
all seven episodes.

02:31.048 --> 02:34.313
- Hey, what the hell's going on?
- If you like great PBS programs...

02:34.418 --> 02:37.148
<i>like Do Shut Up
and Shut Your Gob...</i>

02:37.254 --> 02:39.279
you'll want to support
our pledge drive.

02:39.390 --> 02:42.359
<i>- [ Bart ] Rledge drive? [ Groans ]
- That's right, Betty White.</i>

02:42.459 --> 02:47.226
Absolutely. If you watch even one second
of PBS and don't contribute...

02:47.331 --> 02:49.799
you're a thief- a common thief!.

02:49.900 --> 02:53.961
- Okay, take it easy, Betty.
- Sorry, but these thieves make me so damn mad.

02:54.071 --> 02:58.005
- You know who you are. Thieves!
- You're mad? Where's my show?

02:58.177 --> 03:00.477
And Now it's time to go back
to Do shut up

03:00.577 --> 03:01.377
Finally!

03:01.478 --> 03:01.874
- But first-
- [ Groans ]

03:02.479 --> 03:05.744
With your donation,
you'll receive this classic PBS tote bag.

03:05.849 --> 03:10.047
Or this umbrella, featuring
a picture of our classic tote bag.

03:10.154 --> 03:13.612
And the next 20 callers will get
this album of museum noises.

03:13.724 --> 03:15.624
Now your music room can sound...

03:15.726 --> 03:18.695
just like the Metropolitan
Museum in New York.

03:18.796 --> 03:20.889
<i>[ Footsteps Echoing ]</i>

03:21.932 --> 03:23.900
<i>- [ Man Coughs ]
- Outstanding.</i>

03:24.001 --> 03:26.526
Why are you torturing me?
I'm just a man!

03:26.637 --> 03:30.266
You know, I've worked with so many
legendary actors over the years...

03:30.374 --> 03:33.241
<i>who could be counted on
to ''phone it in.''</i>

03:33.343 --> 03:38.076
Well, now it's your turn to phone it in-
Your pledge, that is.

03:38.182 --> 03:43.381
Please- Please! We're only $10,000 away
from returning to our show.

03:43.487 --> 03:45.819
Well, why didn't you say so?

03:45.923 --> 03:48.687
[ Beeping ]

03:48.792 --> 03:51.192
- [ Line Ringing ]
- Yes, I'd like to pledge $10,000...

03:51.295 --> 03:53.195
to get them to shut up.

03:53.297 --> 03:56.095
From... anonymous.
Done and done.

03:56.200 --> 03:59.397
- Dad, you don't have $10,000.
- Aw, how they gonna find me?

03:59.503 --> 04:01.403
[ Bell Dings ]

04:01.505 --> 04:05.168
Folks, we just reached
our goal of $10,700...

04:05.275 --> 04:10.542
and it's all thanks to one generous caller
who didn't leave his name.

04:10.647 --> 04:13.115
- [ Chuckling ]
- But thanks to Insta-Trace...

04:13.217 --> 04:16.675
we've learned it's Homer Simpson
of 742 Evergreen Terrace.

04:16.786 --> 04:19.915
[ Screams ]
Why did I register with Insta-Trace?

04:20.023 --> 04:23.459
Our pledge enforcement van
will be at his house in moments.

04:23.560 --> 04:25.357
<i>- Uh-oh. You gotta help me, Bart.
- [ Footsteps ]</i>

04:25.462 --> 04:27.726
That's it, boy! Go get help.

04:27.831 --> 04:29.731
- [ Swing Squeaking ]
- D'oh!

04:39.276 --> 04:41.437
Okay, Homer, don't panic.

04:41.545 --> 04:43.570
Let me do the talking.

04:44.882 --> 04:47.373
Here he is, folks,
the man who saved PBS...

04:47.484 --> 04:51.011
- Homer Simpson.
- [ Cheering ]

04:51.121 --> 04:53.021
[ Cheering On TV]

04:53.123 --> 04:55.318
Mom, Dad's on PBS.

04:55.425 --> 04:58.553
Hmm? They don't show
police chases, do they?

04:58.662 --> 05:02.063
Um, it's an honor to give $10,000...

05:02.166 --> 05:06.296
especially now, when the rich mosaic
of cable programming...

05:06.403 --> 05:12.035
- has made public television
so very, very unnecessary.
- [ Scattered Applause ]

05:12.142 --> 05:15.771
- From now on, one of us always stays home.
- Agreed.

05:15.879 --> 05:19.406
Well said, Homer. And now
for the moment of generosity.

05:19.516 --> 05:22.417
- Will cash be okay?
- Absolutely!

05:22.519 --> 05:26.319
- Well, then we got a problem.
The banks are closed by now.
- It's 12:15.

05:26.423 --> 05:28.948
Maybe your movie star banks
are open crazy hours...

05:29.059 --> 05:31.357
but we in Springfield
are simple folk.

05:31.461 --> 05:36.160
We like our cars fast
and our banks closed. Uh-

05:36.266 --> 05:39.702
Okay, fine. We'll go down there,
but they're not going to be open.

05:41.438 --> 05:44.373
Yeah. It's a real ghost town in there.

05:44.474 --> 05:46.772
[ Chuckles ]
Get in there.

05:48.478 --> 05:52.437
I'd like to withdraw $10,000, please.

05:52.549 --> 05:55.746
<i>''You are on television. Please play along.''
Are you robbing me?</i>

05:55.852 --> 05:57.911
[ Whispering ]
I'll pay you later.

05:58.021 --> 06:00.421
- Um, is there a problem, Mr. Simpson?
- Uh, why, no.

06:00.524 --> 06:03.322
Everything is just-
[ Grunting ]

06:04.361 --> 06:06.693
[ Wails ]

06:06.797 --> 06:10.358
I can't do it. I can't kill a man.

06:10.467 --> 06:12.458
[ Grunting ]

06:12.569 --> 06:16.232
- You don't have the money, do you, Homer?
- Mm-mmm.

06:16.340 --> 06:18.934
And you thought
you could stab your problems away?

06:19.042 --> 06:20.942
- Mm-hmm.
- Silly goose.

06:21.044 --> 06:23.706
Why didn't you say so?
Get him, boys.

06:25.115 --> 06:27.743
- [ Screams ] The hooligans!
- Bash his eyes out!

06:27.851 --> 06:31.287
- [ Screams ]
- [ Clamoring ]

06:34.491 --> 06:37.289
It's a beautiful day to kick your ass!

06:37.394 --> 06:40.454
- You die now!
- [ Shouts ]

06:41.865 --> 06:44.026
[ Whimpering ]

06:45.802 --> 06:48.669
- [ Screeching ]
- [ Whimpering ]

06:50.574 --> 06:52.542
Bingo!

06:56.680 --> 07:00.707
Sanctuary! Sanctuary!

07:00.817 --> 07:04.253
Oh, why did I teach him that word?

07:04.354 --> 07:06.254
Quick. You gotta hide me from PBS.

07:06.356 --> 07:09.917
Their bloodthirsty pursuit is made possible
by a grant from the Chubb Group.

07:12.429 --> 07:16.024
- Give us the money!
- Elmo knows where you live.

07:16.133 --> 07:18.465
Please, help me. I'll do anything.
I'll light a candle.

07:18.568 --> 07:20.502
I'll help with your next charity scam.

07:20.604 --> 07:23.129
<i>- The word is ''drive.''
- Sure, sure. Bob's your uncle.</i>

07:23.240 --> 07:25.174
Let's just get out of here.

07:25.275 --> 07:28.073
[ Clamoring ]

07:32.649 --> 07:34.549
[ Clears Throat ]
Nothing to see here, people.

07:34.651 --> 07:37.449
Just headed down to the dump
with these children's letters to God.

07:37.554 --> 07:39.454
[ Whimpering ]

07:39.556 --> 07:41.490
[ Tires Squealing ]

07:45.862 --> 07:48.422
We'll send you someplace safe
till the heat dies down.

07:48.532 --> 07:50.796
Great, but why am I on a plane?

07:50.901 --> 07:55.395
Homer, how would you like to be
a missionary in the South Pacific?

07:55.505 --> 07:57.735
South Pacific? I didn't agree to-

07:59.476 --> 08:01.671
[ Whimpers ]
W-Wait!

08:01.778 --> 08:05.373
<i>I'm no missionary.
I don't even believe in ''Jebus.''</i>

08:05.482 --> 08:08.212
- Let me out.
- Sorry. No can do.

08:08.318 --> 08:11.185
[ Whimpers, Grunts ]

08:12.656 --> 08:15.682
Oh, save me,Jebus!

08:22.332 --> 08:24.300
Mmm.

08:24.401 --> 08:26.869
[ Chuckles, Sighs ]

08:28.705 --> 08:31.003
Mmm!
[ Smacks Lips ]

08:31.108 --> 08:33.008
Oh- Little piece there.

08:33.110 --> 08:36.010
<i>- [ Smacking ] Mmm.
- [ Clears Throat ]</i>

08:36.113 --> 08:39.082
So, you said on the phone
you had something to tell me?

08:39.182 --> 08:42.309
Mmm? Oh, yes.
Your husband's in Micro-Asia.

08:42.419 --> 08:45.718
- [ Gasps ]
- Micro-Asia? That's 1 2,000 miles away.

08:45.822 --> 08:47.949
Uh-huh. He needed
to get away for a while.

08:48.058 --> 08:51.357
I suggested missionary work,
and he jumped at the idea.

08:51.461 --> 08:54.089
- Missionary work?
- He's dead, isn't he?

08:54.197 --> 08:58.190
No, no. You can even keep in touch
with him on this ham radio.

08:58.301 --> 09:00.792
- [ Static ]
- [ Homer] Jebus, where are you?

09:00.904 --> 09:04.601
Homer toJebus.
[ Moans ]

09:09.980 --> 09:12.540
[ Groans, Grunts ]
Ooh.

09:12.649 --> 09:15.345
This doesn't look so bad.

09:15.452 --> 09:18.319
Ah. Hi there, little fella.

09:19.489 --> 09:21.457
Well, what the-
Wh-Wh-What-

09:21.558 --> 09:23.458
[ Whimpering ]

09:23.560 --> 09:25.858
Huh?
[ Whimpers, Sighs ]

09:25.962 --> 09:28.055
Welcome aboard, brother.
You must be Homer.

09:28.165 --> 09:30.224
I'm Craig. That's Amy.

09:30.333 --> 09:33.769
- Well, see ya.
- You're leaving? Wait. What do I do here?

09:33.870 --> 09:37.067
First of all, forget everything
you learned in missionary school.

09:37.174 --> 09:39.335
- Done.
- We taught them some English...

09:39.443 --> 09:41.604
and ridiculed away
most of their beliefs.

09:41.711 --> 09:44.236
So you can take it from there. Bye!

09:44.347 --> 09:46.281
Don't let the bedbugs bite.

09:46.383 --> 09:48.442
Seriously.

09:53.457 --> 09:56.585
Me Homer. Me hiding from PBS.

09:56.693 --> 10:00.094
I am Q'Toktok, and this is Ak.

10:02.399 --> 10:06.233
Welcome, Reverend Homer. We look forward
to learning about the Bible from you.

10:07.604 --> 10:10.004
- Here you go. Knock yourself out.
- We cannot read.

10:10.106 --> 10:13.564
<i>[ Groans ] Does the word ''jet lag''
mean anything to you people?</i>

10:13.677 --> 10:15.668
<i>Jet... lag?</i>

10:19.115 --> 10:21.345
Are you enjoying your ox testicle?

10:21.451 --> 10:23.351
Oh, yes. Very much so.

10:23.453 --> 10:26.889
Really? You sure you
wouldn't rather have a coconut?

10:26.990 --> 10:28.924
[ Chuckles ]
They're delicious.

10:29.025 --> 10:31.323
No, I'm good.

10:33.063 --> 10:35.554
Mmm. Hey, what happened
to all the shirtless girls...

10:35.665 --> 10:37.633
you see in all the geographical magazines?

10:37.734 --> 10:40.794
Craig and Amy gave us
the gift of shame.

10:40.904 --> 10:43.668
<i>All the naked women
are on that island.</i>

10:43.773 --> 10:47.140
- [ Drums, Laughter]
- Yeah, anything goes over there.

10:47.244 --> 10:49.337
- Bouncy, bouncy.
- [ Groans ]

10:49.446 --> 10:51.380
<i>- [ Deep Rumbling ]
- What was that?</i>

10:51.481 --> 10:55.110
Oh, we call that-
[ Choking Sounds ]

10:56.853 --> 10:59.981
<i>Sorry. Fish bone in my throat.
We call that ''earthquake.''</i>

11:00.090 --> 11:02.888
Great. Now my testicle's got ants on it.

11:05.795 --> 11:08.093
Thanks, sweetheart. Have a Bible.

11:08.198 --> 11:10.632
My name's Homer. What's yours?

11:10.734 --> 11:13.168
I am Ouilouiyukitanawanje.

11:14.905 --> 11:17.237
I'm gonna call you Lisa Jr.

11:17.340 --> 11:19.638
So, what do you do
for fun around here?

11:19.743 --> 11:23.270
Craig and Amy were digging a well.

11:23.380 --> 11:26.178
Craig and Amy were also
building a chapel.

11:26.283 --> 11:29.810
Craig and Amy, Craig and Amy.
Why don't you just marry Craig and Amy?

11:29.920 --> 11:32.616
I told you we should have asked them.

11:32.722 --> 11:35.350
How's the TV reception here? Excellent or-

11:35.458 --> 11:38.154
- T... V?
- You don't have TV?

11:38.261 --> 11:40.889
But what will I watch
while I'm sitting on the couch?

11:40.997 --> 11:44.228
- Couch?
- No couches either?

11:44.334 --> 11:46.598
Oh, man, I need a beer.

11:49.005 --> 11:52.406
[ Gasps ]
Oh, God, oh, God, oh, God, oh, God!

11:52.509 --> 11:55.569
[ Together]
Oh, God, oh, God, oh, God, oh, God!

12:00.083 --> 12:02.210
[ Slurping ]

12:03.286 --> 12:05.186
Nothin'.

12:05.288 --> 12:07.188
[ Slurping ]
Here we go.

12:07.290 --> 12:09.656
[ Chuckling ]
Yeah.

12:09.759 --> 12:12.785
[ Marge's Voice ]
Homer? Homer!

12:12.896 --> 12:14.591
Huh? What the-

12:14.698 --> 12:17.064
[ Echoing ]
Hello!

12:17.167 --> 12:19.328
Is there anybody in there?

12:19.436 --> 12:21.461
Marge!

12:21.571 --> 12:23.198
Homer, are you all right?

12:23.306 --> 12:25.331
I guess so.
But that first month was pretty rough.

12:25.442 --> 12:27.103
You've only been gone two days.

12:27.210 --> 12:29.303
Really? Without TV
it's hard to know...

12:29.412 --> 12:31.346
when one day begins
and the other ends.

12:31.448 --> 12:34.383
<i>I miss you, Dad. Mom won't
let me read Hägar the Horrible.</i>

12:34.484 --> 12:36.418
I just don't think it's funny.

12:36.519 --> 12:40.478
Hmm. I can see the house is falling apart
without me, so here's the new order.

12:40.590 --> 12:42.490
<i>- Bart,you're the man of the house.
- Mmm!</i>

12:42.592 --> 12:44.492
- Lisa, I'm promoting you to boy.
- [ Growls ]

12:44.594 --> 12:46.494
<i>Maggie's now the brainy girl.</i>

12:46.596 --> 12:48.188
<i>Toaster can fill in for Maggie.</i>

12:48.298 --> 12:51.165
<i>- And, Marge,you're a consultant.
- [ Groans ]</i>

12:51.267 --> 12:53.132
- Dad?
- Yes, boy?

12:53.236 --> 12:55.227
I just want to tell you
how proud I am...

12:55.338 --> 12:57.431
that you're showing
an interest in your fellow man.

12:57.540 --> 13:00.338
Really? You're proud of me?

13:00.443 --> 13:03.901
Oh, yes. The whole town thinks
you're a real humanitarian.

13:04.014 --> 13:06.710
Ned Flanders is green with envy.

13:06.816 --> 13:08.784
Oh, really?

13:08.885 --> 13:10.876
Well, if you'll excuse me...

13:10.987 --> 13:13.751
I got some civilization
to spread like butter...

13:13.857 --> 13:16.758
on the English muffin
that is these people...

13:16.860 --> 13:19.385
with all their little nooks and crannies.

13:19.496 --> 13:21.361
Dad, are you licking toads?

13:21.464 --> 13:23.432
<i>I'm not not licking toads.</i>

13:23.533 --> 13:25.433
Well, it's time to get to work.

13:25.535 --> 13:28.595
Humanitarian Homer Simpson,
over and out.

13:30.640 --> 13:32.904
- [ Croaks ]
- [ Slurping ]

13:33.943 --> 13:36.377
- [ Croaks ]
- [ Giggles ]

13:36.479 --> 13:39.937
Gather round, everyone.
I'm gonna teach you about religion.

13:40.050 --> 13:42.382
[ Together]
Oh, God, oh, God, oh, God-

13:42.485 --> 13:44.544
- Please, please. That's not necessary.
- oh, God, oh, God-

13:44.654 --> 13:46.952
I'm just God's messenger.

13:47.057 --> 13:50.458
And lo, what a wondrous message it is.

13:50.560 --> 13:53.358
Like this, from the book of...

13:53.463 --> 13:55.363
<i>''P-salms.''</i>

13:55.465 --> 13:58.593
<i>''God will shatter the heads
of his enemies...</i>

13:58.702 --> 14:01.865
<i>''the hairy crown of those
who walk in their guilty ways...</i>

14:01.971 --> 14:04.235
that you may bathe
your feet in blood.''

14:04.340 --> 14:08.800
As true today as it was
when it was written.

14:08.912 --> 14:11.403
Now let's open it up
to some Q&A.

14:11.514 --> 14:13.209
Yes, Lisa Jr.?

14:13.316 --> 14:16.774
Amy said there are lots of religions.
Which is the right one?

14:16.886 --> 14:20.481
Well, not the Unitarians.
If that's the one true faith, I'll eat my hat.

14:20.590 --> 14:23.024
Um, if the Lord is all-powerful...

14:23.126 --> 14:25.651
why does he care whether
we worship him or not?

14:25.762 --> 14:27.696
[ Chuckles ]
Ak just saying.

14:27.797 --> 14:32.894
Well, Ak, it's because God is powerful,
but also insecure-

14:33.002 --> 14:35.800
like Barbra Streisand
beforeJames Brolin.

14:35.905 --> 14:37.805
Oh, he's been a rock.

14:39.876 --> 14:42.606
Oh, who am I kidding?
The truth is I'm no missionary.

14:42.712 --> 14:45.237
I work in a nuclear power plant.

14:45.348 --> 14:48.943
Ooh. Tell us all you know
about nuclear power.

14:50.687 --> 14:53.451
Look, the point is, I want to help.

14:53.556 --> 14:57.151
But you don't need a well or a chapel
or an immunization center.

14:57.260 --> 14:59.751
What you need's a little razzle-dazzle.

14:59.863 --> 15:03.230
[ Gasps ]
Q'Toktok, are you thinking what I'm thinking?

15:03.333 --> 15:07.269
- I am Ak.
- Hey, that's great. Now let's get to work.

15:09.105 --> 15:11.096
<i>Now, if The Flintstones
has taught us anything...</i>

15:11.207 --> 15:14.404
it's that pelicans can be used
to mix cement.

15:14.511 --> 15:16.445
Come on, little friend.
Make a wisecrack.

15:16.546 --> 15:19.743
<i>You know- ''It's a living.''
That sort of thing.</i>

15:19.849 --> 15:23.182
<i>- Oopsy.
- [ Bird Caws ]</i>

15:25.021 --> 15:26.955
- Hiya, Homer.
- That's not Homer.

15:27.056 --> 15:29.251
It's gotta be.
He's parking in Homer's space.

15:33.530 --> 15:35.896
Well, time to get to work. Mmm.

15:35.999 --> 15:37.557
- Simpson!
- Aah!

15:37.667 --> 15:41.535
I've just reviewed your 1 0-year
performance record, and it's appalling.

15:41.638 --> 15:44.766
- But I'm not Homer Simpson.
- I think I know who Homer Simpson is.

15:44.874 --> 15:48.901
In 1 0 short years
you've caused 1 7 meltdowns.

15:49.012 --> 15:50.639
- One is too many.
- Yeah, but-

15:50.747 --> 15:54.046
You sold weapons-grade plutonium
to the Iraqis-with no markup.

15:54.150 --> 15:56.050
- But-
- And worst of all...

15:56.152 --> 15:59.053
<i>you took the Hamburglar's birthday off
last Monday and Wednesday.</i>

15:59.155 --> 16:01.055
Which is it?
[ Exhales ]

16:01.157 --> 16:04.615
Now, my voice is giving out, so I'm just
going to poke you for the next hour or so.

16:04.727 --> 16:07.287
[ Both Grunting ]

16:07.397 --> 16:09.490
[ Sighs ]

16:09.599 --> 16:12.397
Friends, when I came here
one month ago...

16:12.502 --> 16:15.437
this seemed like a strange
and frightening place.

16:15.538 --> 16:18.905
But now I've learned
to love this island as my second-

16:19.008 --> 16:22.569
A plane! Stop!
Get me off this stinkin' rock!

16:22.679 --> 16:24.613
[ Groans ]
Anyhoo-

16:24.714 --> 16:27.808
I'm about to share with you
a modern-day miracle-

16:27.917 --> 16:32.786
Something that has revitalized cities
from East Saint Louis to Biloxi, Mississippi.

16:32.889 --> 16:35.517
The magic medicine of...

16:35.625 --> 16:37.923
casino gambling!

16:41.331 --> 16:45.131
<i>- ''The Lucky Savage''?
- It could be you.</i>

16:46.870 --> 16:48.770
Check it out-There's island blackjack...

16:48.872 --> 16:51.466
island craps, island Texas hold 'em.

16:51.574 --> 16:54.839
But if, like me, you're mesmerized
by pretty colors and spinning things...

16:54.944 --> 16:56.844
you'll prefer roulette.

16:56.946 --> 16:59.881
Four sand dollars
on number six, please.

16:59.983 --> 17:02.816
[ Rattling ]

17:04.854 --> 17:08.085
- So how you doin'? Stayin' out of trouble?
- Yes, sir.

17:09.259 --> 17:11.454
- Number six.
- Whoo-hoo!

17:11.560 --> 17:13.461
<i>D'oh!</i>

17:13.563 --> 17:16.259
Now over here I've brewed up
my favorite beverage.

17:16.366 --> 17:20.462
Beer. It's mostly Dristan and holy water,
but it does the job.

17:20.569 --> 17:23.164
<i>[ Slurps ]
Mmm. ''Ooga-booga.''</i>

17:23.272 --> 17:26.106
- [ Chattering ]
- So have fun, everybody.

17:26.209 --> 17:30.202
And who knows? Maybe you'll
hit the jackpot, get off this island...

17:30.313 --> 17:33.578
and spend the rest of your days
in a tropical paradise.

17:33.683 --> 17:35.913
- [ Chattering ]
- Okay!

17:37.887 --> 17:39.650
- Yea!
- [ Chattering ]

17:42.525 --> 17:46.586
Homer, I'm so impressed.
Everything you're doing sounds so rewarding.

17:46.696 --> 17:48.960
Oh, you should have
seen their faces, honey.

17:49.065 --> 17:51.727
Now I know how Bob Stupak feels.

17:51.834 --> 17:55.133
## [ Whistling ]

17:55.238 --> 17:58.036
Is everybody happy?

17:58.141 --> 18:00.132
<i>[ Shouting, Screaming ]</i>

18:05.148 --> 18:07.207
- Huh?
- [ Clamoring ]

18:07.317 --> 18:09.217
- [ Groans ]
- Oh, my God.

18:09.319 --> 18:12.049
<i>How can ace be one and 1 1 ?</i>

18:12.155 --> 18:15.283
Huh? What kind of god
would allow that?

18:15.391 --> 18:17.689
[ Grunts ]

18:17.794 --> 18:19.728
[ Groans ]

18:21.831 --> 18:26.700
- [ Clamoring ]
- [ Gasps ] Oh, what happened?

18:26.803 --> 18:32.298
I gave you a glittering Vegas
and you turned it into a scanty Atlantic City.

18:32.408 --> 18:35.605
Your alcohol and inexpensive buffets
have corrupted us.

18:35.712 --> 18:37.839
I don't even like macaroni salad...

18:37.947 --> 18:40.472
but look at me!
[ Chomping ]

18:44.053 --> 18:45.953
Please help us.

18:46.055 --> 18:49.422
Our island has not been this damaged
since the A-bomb tests.

18:53.196 --> 18:55.096
[ Groans ]

18:55.198 --> 18:57.428
Guess who I saw
at the supermarket today.

18:57.533 --> 19:00.001
Can it wait? I just got off work.

19:00.103 --> 19:02.003
I'm sorry, honey.
I just thought you-

19:02.105 --> 19:04.164
Don't you do enough yakkin'
at the beauty parlor?

19:04.273 --> 19:08.039
<i>That's it, Bart. You're taking
this ''man of the house'' thing too far.</i>

19:08.144 --> 19:10.078
You're right. I'm sorry.
Tell you what.

19:10.179 --> 19:12.739
Saturday night, we'll go out for steaks-
just you and me.

19:12.849 --> 19:15.818
Hmm. A night out is a night out.

19:15.918 --> 19:17.886
[ Grunting ]

19:20.757 --> 19:23.692
[ Speaking Native Language ]

19:27.830 --> 19:30.196
Why are you building chapel?

19:30.299 --> 19:33.325
- Because you're all terrible sinners.
- Since when?

19:33.436 --> 19:35.336
Since I got here.

19:35.438 --> 19:37.804
Now either grab a stone or go to hell.

19:37.907 --> 19:39.932
[ All Gasp ]

19:40.043 --> 19:42.273
[ Grunting ]

19:44.881 --> 19:47.509
Well, I may not know
much about God...

19:47.617 --> 19:51.383
but I have to say, we built
a pretty nice cage for him.

19:51.487 --> 19:54.888
- [ Chattering ]
- These are from the children.

19:54.991 --> 19:57.653
Thanks to you, all of us
finally have a place to pray.

19:57.760 --> 20:02.424
<i>- Aw.
- And I'm in a gambling program.
For real this time.</i>

20:02.532 --> 20:05.592
How many times must we
go to church to avoid hell?

20:05.701 --> 20:07.794
Every Sunday for the rest of our lives.

20:07.904 --> 20:09.872
[ Laughs ]
No, really.

20:09.972 --> 20:13.237
<i>[ Chiming ]</i>

20:15.044 --> 20:17.205
Not bad, Lisa Jr.

20:17.313 --> 20:20.407
But God's palace
is way up on the moon.

20:20.516 --> 20:23.280
[ Slurping ]
So if you want him to hear us...

20:23.386 --> 20:25.616
we've gotta crank up the volume.

20:25.721 --> 20:27.780
- [ Chiming Louder]
- Do you hear me, Lord?

20:27.890 --> 20:30.085
Homer's doin' your work!

20:30.193 --> 20:34.357
- I'm the greatest missionary of all time!
- [ Rumbling ]

20:34.464 --> 20:36.830
[ Clamoring ]

20:39.669 --> 20:42.160
[ Whimpering ]

20:57.820 --> 21:00.948
Oh, no! This looks like the end.

21:01.057 --> 21:03.252
[ Both Screaming ]

21:05.228 --> 21:08.755
[ Laughing ]
Oh, that Homer- always getting into trouble.

21:08.865 --> 21:12.028
And if you're one of the millions
who enjoys his adventures-

21:12.135 --> 21:14.069
<i>or should I say misadventures-</i>

21:14.170 --> 21:16.104
<i>it's time to show your support.</i>

21:16.205 --> 21:18.435
Sure, Fox makes a fortune
from advertising...

21:18.541 --> 21:21.772
- but it's still not enough.
- Not nearly enough!

21:21.878 --> 21:26.838
So if you don't want to see crude, lowbrow
programming disappear from the airwaves...

21:26.949 --> 21:29.247
please, call now.

21:29.352 --> 21:31.047
[ Rings ]

21:31.154 --> 21:33.748
[ With Australian Accent ]
Hello! Murdoch here.

21:33.856 --> 21:35.790
$10,000!

21:35.892 --> 21:37.792
You've saved my network.

21:37.894 --> 21:40.454
Wouldn't be the first time.

22:25.942 --> 22:27.569
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

22:27.677 --> 22:30.771
<i>[ Homer]
Save me,Jebus!</i>

